THIS IS A MODIFIED COPY OF SPECFEM3D_GLOBE version 7.0.0 [2015-07-10] WHICH IS EXTENDED
FOR USE WITH ASKI versions 1.0 to 1.2 AND IS AVAILABLE VIA
https://github.com/seismology-RUB/SPECFEM3D_GLOBE_for_ASKI , subdirectory specfem3d_globe/
SOME FOLDERS LIKE utils, doc, EXAMPLES/* ETC. WERE REMOVED TO KEEP THIS COPY SMALL


THE ORIGINAL FILE "README.md" WAS RENAMED "README.md.original"


IN FILE setup/constants.h.in , "ASSUME_PERFECT_SPHERE" was set to ".true."


THE ADDITIONAL SUBFOLDER 
EXAMPLES/ASKI_small/ 
WAS ADDED CONTAINING ALL RELEVANT FILES THAT WERE USED TO PRODUCE THE EXAMPLE 
ASKI_example_spherical_small.tar.gz AVAILABLE VIA 
https://github.com/seismology-RUB/ASKI/releases/tag/v1.0


ON YOUR SYSTEM, YOU NEED TO CONFIGURE AND COMPILE AGAIN, e.g.:
> ./configure FC=gfortran MPIFC=mpif90
> make xmeshfem3D xspecfem3D


